76561198005755324,Recommended,302080,24155627,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,Mr. Tex,"I've played the downloadable version a fair bit but re-bought it on Steam for convenience. It's a fun causal driving game. Compared to ETS/ATS and OMSI it's quite arcade, however that does not mean the game is easy (let alone not fun). It's a challenge to keep the passengers happy and arrive at the stops within time. However that's partly where the replay value lies. It's a game I do replay every now and then because other bus driving games don't offer the same variety as this one does, not without buying a whole bunch of expensive DLCs. Personally I see it as a nice complement to the more hardcore bus driving sims. It works well with a 360 controller. For me it runs perfectly on Windows 10, for others it doesn't."
