,Recommended,302080,22327972,"Posted: 9 April, 2016",all,1singur,"This is obviously a niche game, so unless you know what you're buying, be prepared for disappointment. The game is great for what it is, but it is what it is: a slow paced game meant to simulate real life scenarios. If you enjoy speeding down the street in your fast car while playing GTA or NFS, this game might not be for you. Also, SCS' trucking games are different too, because between cities, they don't have that many rules to keep you tied. Bus Simulator feels more restricted, because you play in an urban area. You have to mind the street lights, the cops, watch your speed, be considerate of your passengers, etc... This all means the game is not bad, but it ain't for everybody either."
