,Recommended,302080,16044634,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,wüf,"This game's..interesting. It lacks any flair or fancy, has no real incentives for the player to actually keep playing, beyond holding off more difficult levels until a few levels from easier tiers are completed, and it's virtually impossible to play without a controller (You can get along fine with just WASD, but good luck braking at red lights/bus stops without being penalised for braking too hard).That being said, it's oddly alright to just waste time and chill in? As a game I didn't even know I had in my steam library until a few weeks ago, it's decent enough. Don't pay full price for it, though. I'm recommending this for anyone who is unsure of playing it after discovering they own it, or for anyone considering purchasing a bundle including this game, or purchasing this game alone when heavily discounted.To sum it up in bullet points:+ Decent difficulty curve+ Has some unexpected variations on some levels+ One of the very few driving sim games I've played that actually penalises you for not indicating before switching lanes- You essentially -need- a gamepad with pressure sensitivity to play, as keyboard controls mean avoiding braking too hard is near impossible- AI vehicles in-game go between 0 and full-speed instantly, making negotiating red lights difficult if there's anyone in front in your lane- On some levels, the spawn point is off the side of the road, and you must drive across oncoming traffic to head in the right direction. The game seems unaware that it has imposed this upon you, and will penalise you for driving on the wrong side of the road as you cross over."
