76561198159426714,Recommended,302080,19710259,"Posted: 15 December, 2015",all,nzyowie,"This is no OMSI 2 or Euro Truck Simulator 2, but for an older game it's pretty good fun. The graphics, bearing in mind the age of the game, are excellent. Steering is OK, and a LOT better than the steering in Bus Simulator 2012, although not as good as the steering in OMSI 2. You get a good range of scenarios, and passing them helps to unlock higher-level ones. The scenarios are nice and varied, with some set in the city, some in the suburbs and some out in the country. The weather in the scenarios is also highly varied. You get to drive in snow, rain, wind and of course bright sunshine. So you get a good range of driving experiences.One thing the game lacks is a bus interior. You only get two camera views: behind the bus from the outside or perched on the front windscreen. So you can't see your steering wheel, dashboard and so on. Another gripe I have is that the traffic lights are kind of hard to see and also seem to have very short sequences.This is not a sophisticated simulator like OMSI 2 or the SCS flagship Euro Truck Simulator 2. It is also not as sophisticated as Bus Simulator 2012, but is far more functional than the latter and thus more enjoyable to play. Definitely a very good early offering from SCS. I look forward to trying out their Euro Coach Simulator at some stage in the future!"
