,Recommended,302080,21314957,"Posted: 19 February, 2016",all,Raven Almasy,"When I first saw this game on steam I didn't think it was a serious game. Probably because I was in a not so serious mood. Reading the reviews at that time I still could not believe it was a serious game. I was under the impression it would just be a game where you could screw over passengers and what not. Hours later I was not busy trying to cause accidents but I was busy trying to be a responsible bus driver. This game became very serious.I really enjoy this game. Driving on the highway has never been this calming. You just have to put on some background music and off you go! This game even got me to use blinkers! I have never bothered in any game with blinkers but in this game I really do try my best to keep to the rules of the road.Ofcourse no game is without a flaw or two and the same goes for bus driver. My biggest annoyance with this game is the timer. I understand that, as a bus driver, you need to be on time at the next stop. However, especially in later levels, this is almost impossible to do. Even if you were to drive through red lights (point deduction of 200) you will not make it. I suppose thats realistic as most of the time bus drivers are not in time but seeing as how it does count up at the end of the level I feel that that could have been made a little better. Not to mention that no matter which bus I drive there is an automatic speed limit on it. There are other busses in the same level that are going faster then I am.All in all it's a nice game to play. If you have some money to spare and you would like a nice calming game and ignore the flaws that I mentioned then get this game. :)"
